CharDuty.Notes: After being betrayed by the Empire his eyes were opened to their injustice & cruelty and is dedicated to defeating them.

Character.Story:
As a young man Lorne believed in the ideals of a new Empire that could get things done, protect the galaxy and keep the peace. He eagerly volunteered to do his part and served as a Stormtrooper in the Imperial Army.
He quickly demonstrated his dedication and aptitude on various missions gaining the respect from his squad as well as drawing praise from ranking officers.
However, his is immediate commanding officer Lieutenant Zan Ryen was jealous of his abilities and only saw Lorne as a threat. To eliminate Lorne, Lieutenant Zan sent his squad on a suicide mission and then deliberately abandoned them failing to provide the necessary backup.
The squad was massacred with Lorne being the lone survivor. Critically wounded, Lorne was forsaken and left for dead. In Lieutenant Zan's official report he pinned the blame on Lorne accusing him of disobeying a direct order. Against all odds Lorne managed to make his way back to the base critically injured. Instead of being honored as a hero he was court marshalled & dishonorably discharged based on Lieutenant Zans false report. Lorne's faith in his idealistic Empire was quickly dispelled due to the corruption he experienced.
Taking advantage of the situation a Rebel intelligence officer learned of Lorne's situation & recruited him to the alliance to right the wrongs of this corrupt government.
A Quote: "The best revenge is to live on and prove oneself."
